ability to cut funds out of the budget.

46
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:23,583
So I wanted people to understand that because the emails are starting to pour in, thinking that it's the city council that cut all these people's jobs and it wasn't.

47
00:04:24,124 --> 00:04:32,547
So, but again, I opened this up for discussion with my fellow councillors and maybe this will speed the process up for the mayor a little bit.

48
00:04:33,407 --> 00:04:34,108
Thank you, Mr. President.

49
00:04:34,428 --> 00:04:35,588
Thank you, Vice President Carvajal.

50
00:04:35,628 --> 00:04:39,550
We have Councilor Scott Kelly, Councilor Morrell, Councilor Beers, Councilor Scott Kelly.

51
00:04:40,213 --> 00:04:44,456
Thank you, Mr. President, and thank you, Councilor Carviello for bringing this forward.

52
00:04:44,476 --> 00:05:00,085
I know that to jump to my second piece, I did receive a bunch of emails that a school committee member sent out stating this year we are facing a $3.5 million budget

53
00:05:02,218 --> 00:05:10,944
that the cuts are right now, the school committee and superintendent cannot direct city funding, only the mayor and the city council.

54
00:05:11,405 --> 00:05:22,873
So what's happening is people taking that comment, whichever way that school member meant to put that out there, the way that it's going out to the public is again, it's starting that divide.

55
00:05:23,974 --> 00:05:25,755
It's what's wrong with the city council?

56
00:05:26,196 --> 00:05:27,637
Why are you not funding these people?

57
00:05:28,543 --> 00:05:29,964
Why, what are you doing?

58
00:05:30,304 --> 00:05:30,964
We need this.

59
00:05:31,744 --> 00:05:39,788
So again, it's been a very difficult last couple of weeks, but I tell you what, this is where we do not have to go as a community.

60
00:05:40,728 --> 00:05:41,909
This is so disheartening.

61
00:05:42,649 --> 00:05:47,431
I'm sorry, Councilor Falco, the One Medford, it's so farthest from the truth right now.

62
00:05:47,531 --> 00:05:48,531
It's so disheartening.

63
00:05:48,872 --> 00:05:51,673
That's what I've heard for the last three nights especially.

64
00:05:52,293 --> 00:05:56,355
I'm telling you that please, maybe the city solicitor,

65
00:05:57,143 --> 00:06:10,388
can reach out to the mayor with a highlight of what the role of the city council is during the budget in comparison to the school department.

66
00:06:11,148 --> 00:06:18,031
Because I know when we were on the school committee, we were given a tutorial and we understood exactly what the process was.

67
00:06:19,011 --> 00:06:20,152
Brings me to my first point.

68
00:06:20,832 --> 00:06:26,194
In the late 1990s, early 2000s, I was given my pink slip as a teacher in the city of Medford.

69
00:06:27,075 --> 00:06:31,098
It's probably the most devastating feeling you'll ever, ever feel.

70
00:06:32,038 --> 00:06:33,059
It's a helpless feeling.

71
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,381
And I, too, are getting all the emails.

72
00:06:36,541 --> 00:06:43,525
I have former colleagues calling me and relatives calling me and saying, George, what are we doing?

73
00:06:45,566 --> 00:06:51,150
We'll know more as soon as we start our process on Saturday, I believe.

74
00:06:52,027 --> 00:06:56,990
if you correct me from wrong, I believe we're starting our process on Saturday on the city side.

75
00:06:57,890 --> 00:06:58,170
Correct.

76
00:06:58,691 --> 00:07:10,497
But I want people to understand, we as a council will do everything we can to make sure that we're supporting our colleagues in city government.

77
00:07:10,897 --> 00:07:18,421
I think that as myself, I'm speaking for myself, but I have skin in the game like most of our councils here.

78
00:07:19,408 --> 00:07:23,171
We have children that are in the school system.

79
00:07:24,451 --> 00:07:25,632
My son's a senior.

80
00:07:25,652 --> 00:07:31,656
When I found out today, one of the cuts is we do not have a head of guidance at Medford High School.

81
00:07:32,457 --> 00:07:33,417
To me, that's appalling.

82
00:07:34,498 --> 00:07:41,303
I think that's terrible, especially what we're seeing, what's going to happen as kids return back to school.

83
00:07:43,152 --> 00:07:53,139
with the COVID crisis and not having someone in that position to lead what needs to be led is to me a very, very slippery slope.

84
00:07:54,300 --> 00:08:03,547
But again, again, I have to sit back as a counselor and look at this objectively and say, this is very difficult.

85
00:08:03,647 --> 00:08:07,850
We're asking the school system to cut three and a half million dollars from a budget.

86
00:08:11,282 --> 00:08:23,770
So everybody's, I've also gotten contact that, you know, I got one email saying that we drastically underfund the school system for years while the city gets fatter and fatter.

87
00:08:23,790 --> 00:08:27,413
I don't know if it was meant literally, but I'm going to tell you something.

88
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:34,137
We haven't been, we are on, we are on a thin line when it comes to fire, police, DPW.

89
00:08:35,598 --> 00:08:39,361
But we also will be looking at the same difficulties

90
00:08:40,344 --> 00:08:41,225
in the next few weeks.

91
00:08:42,586 --> 00:08:49,633
So I caution everybody to be alarmed, because I'm alarmed as a parent.

92
00:08:50,414 --> 00:08:54,158
As my former colleagues and friends, they're alarmed as teachers.

93
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:57,882
The word gets out to the children, they're alarmed.

94
00:08:57,922 --> 00:09:00,825
My children are alarmed from what they've heard some of the teachers that were cut.

95
00:09:01,685 --> 00:09:02,606
So what I'm saying is,

96
00:09:03,621 --> 00:09:04,723
Let's stay focused.

97
00:09:05,063 --> 00:09:19,203
Let's try to get through the next couple of weeks the best we can, not pitting each other against each other, and try to find a way that we can all work together and try to do the best we can in these trying, trying times.

98
00:09:20,098 --> 00:09:24,181
We're no different than Brookline or Winchester or Somerville.

99
00:09:24,422 --> 00:09:26,503
Everybody's cutting, everybody.

100
00:09:27,304 --> 00:09:38,353
And I know we're all waiting for the governor to come down and say, if the federal government's not gonna do it, I'm gonna pull a billion dollars out of the rainy day account, and I'm gonna fund education.

101
00:09:38,754 --> 00:09:43,958
I'm gonna send funding right down to the cities and towns to bring them back.

102
00:09:44,378 --> 00:09:45,960
We can only hope, we can wish,

103
00:09:47,230 --> 00:09:48,411
but that's a possibility.

104
00:09:48,691 --> 00:09:59,519
But again, I'm gonna say it again, please, we've often had school commembers on this meeting in these falls.

105
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:03,923
I hope somebody's here so they can bring it back to their colleagues.

106
00:10:04,523 --> 00:10:09,787
Please do not scream the sky is falling and point fingers.

107
00:10:10,628 --> 00:10:13,590
Let's take a deep breath as a community

108
00:10:15,357 --> 00:10:21,318
find a way to bring it all together, working together to do what's best for our whole community.

109
00:10:22,218 --> 00:10:23,118
Thank you, Mr. President.

110
00:10:24,059 --> 00:10:25,339
Thank you, Councilor Scott Kelly.

111
00:10:26,519 --> 00:10:27,159
Councilor Morrell.

112
00:10:28,339 --> 00:10:29,320
Thank you, Mr. President.

113
00:10:29,760 --> 00:10:34,420
So I thank Vice President Caravella for bringing this forward, but I just have one concern with this.

114
00:10:34,540 --> 00:10:43,162
So it was my understanding that at our most recent budget update, our independent auditor suggested that we use the free cash a certain amount, I think,

115
00:10:43,865 --> 00:10:46,265
$6 million or somewhere around there was referenced.

116
00:10:46,726 --> 00:10:55,027
Obviously that's up to the mayor, but because we could get enough local receipts back to bring us back to the level we're at now and maintain our bond rating.

117
00:10:55,667 --> 00:11:11,770
So considering cuts are already being made that have been referenced and the fact that school will be much more expensive to run, it doesn't seem to me to be in the best interest of our city and our schools to then take any money we might get from a bailout and put that back into free cash.

118
00:11:12,455 --> 00:11:35,250
I feel like because the independent auditor said we're able to get back up to a good level with the receipts coming in, that money that, you know, again, we don't know if this money is ever coming, but if it does come, that be put back in to make up for those cuts that are already happening and bring people on and secure people's jobs and make sure our school is prepared and our city services are prepared for this coming fall.

119
00:11:35,370 --> 00:11:40,814
So unless it's amended, I can't vote for this at this point, just because I don't think

120
00:11:41,379 --> 00:11:46,562
that taking that money and not applying it where it's most needed is the most prudent decision.

121
00:11:47,123 --> 00:11:47,703
So thank you.

122
00:11:48,804 --> 00:11:49,764
Thank you, Councilor Morrell.

123
00:11:50,885 --> 00:11:51,726
Councilor Beers.

124
00:11:52,626 --> 00:11:53,527
Thank you, Mr. President.

125
00:11:55,248 --> 00:11:57,830
I thank everyone who's spoken so far.

126
00:11:57,850 --> 00:12:03,934
I agree with Councilor Morrell's concern around that this money might be better used.

127
00:12:04,494 --> 00:12:05,955
I think one of the big concerns right now

128
00:12:06,543 --> 00:12:13,466
is the average estimate for a school district to go back to school with all the COVID stuff is over a million and a half dollars.

129
00:12:13,506 --> 00:12:15,206
I think that stands for Medford as well.

130
00:12:15,826 --> 00:12:19,348
So, we're in a bad place.

131
00:12:19,868 --> 00:12:22,409
We're cutting significant amounts from the budget.

132
00:12:22,569 --> 00:12:31,072
I mean, as Councilor Morrell said, and I think as Councilor Carviella's motion is intended, the plan is already to cover the deficit with free cash.

133
00:12:31,713 --> 00:12:42,801
even with that in place, we're seeing big cuts and layoffs and positions that won't get filled and, you know, seniors who won't have guidance counselors, you know, head of guidance, I should say.

134
00:12:42,921 --> 00:12:46,864
So that's, you know, the free cash won't get us out of this.

135
00:12:47,444 --> 00:12:53,729
It's not enough to stop cuts on the school side or the city side, which are already in a desperate place.

136
00:12:53,789 --> 00:12:57,011
So yeah, it's certainly, you know,

137
00:12:57,387 --> 00:12:59,328
We can't be making cuts like this right now.

138
00:12:59,388 --> 00:13:09,934
I know that we're in a difficult budget situation, but these are essential services and, you know, students are gonna need more, the city's gonna need more, and we're gonna be asking people to do more with less.

139
00:13:10,014 --> 00:13:12,775
And we know how that turns out and how that's turned out historically.

140
00:13:13,055 --> 00:13:16,897
So, you know, there's not enough free cash to fix this problem is my understanding.

141
00:13:16,917 --> 00:13:17,718
I hope that changes.

142
00:13:19,719 --> 00:13:20,759
Thank you, Councilor Piers.

143
00:13:21,359 --> 00:13:22,180
Vice President Carvill.

144
00:13:23,093 --> 00:13:27,294
You know, Mr. President, you know, Councillor Baird and Councillor Murdoch make good points.

145
00:13:27,654 --> 00:13:31,335
There's not enough money here to fix this problem.

146
00:13:31,675 --> 00:13:36,656
But again, we've already done our major borrowing for the City of Bedford.

147
00:13:37,016 --> 00:13:45,559
So, I mean, the library's been funded, the police station's been funded, so there's no big borrowing projects currently on the horizon right now.

148
00:13:46,319 --> 00:13:49,980
So, and let's say, money is at its lowest point ever.

149
00:13:53,168 --> 00:13:58,312
If this be the case, the mayor is only going to have to come to us and ask us for this money anyways.

150
00:14:00,394 --> 00:14:07,739
I'm trying to give her the leverage so she doesn't have to come to us at budget time.

151
00:14:09,061 --> 00:14:14,485
I know she's talked about spending $6.5 million, but again, you're going to have to vote on this coming down the line.

152
00:14:15,837 --> 00:14:21,258
And if you say you're not going to vote for her because you don't have enough money, then I'm a little confused.

153
00:14:21,298 --> 00:14:24,599
But I'm looking to save as many jobs as I can.

154
00:14:24,839 --> 00:14:28,320
And let me tell you, this is something I haven't supported in the past.

155
00:14:30,020 --> 00:14:31,941
I voted against this myself in the past.

156
00:14:32,901 --> 00:14:35,522
But again, these are difficult times.

157
00:14:36,242 --> 00:14:41,103
And I think we're doing the prudent thing going forward.

158
00:14:42,887 --> 00:14:43,508
for the time being.

159
00:14:43,548 --> 00:14:46,971
And let's say any money comes in, should be replenished back into free cash.

160
00:14:48,051 --> 00:14:49,913
And the word free, it's the people's money.

161
00:14:49,933 --> 00:14:51,034
It's not free.

162
00:14:51,114 --> 00:14:52,255
Nothing in this world is free.

163
00:14:52,775 --> 00:14:59,821
So please don't, I don't know where that term ever came from, but it belongs to the residents of Medford and we should use it as we see fit.

164
00:15:00,542 --> 00:15:02,403
So that's all I have to say, Mr. President, at the moment.

165
00:15:02,824 --> 00:15:04,005
Thank you, Vice President Carviello.

166
00:15:04,025 --> 00:15:05,886
We have Councilor Morrell and then Councilor Marks.

167
00:15:06,286 --> 00:15:06,827
Councilor Morrell.

168
00:15:07,504 --> 00:15:08,244
Thank you, Mr. President.

169
00:15:08,264 --> 00:15:09,805
Yeah, I just wanted to clarify what I was saying.

170
00:15:09,845 --> 00:15:12,647
I'm not saying I'm going to vote against the mayor using free cash.

171
00:15:12,667 --> 00:15:29,955
What I'm saying is the way this current resolution is written, the second part I do disagree with because I think if a federal bailout or a state level bailout or something comes down, that money should then be applied to the cuts that have already been made and to secure positions within the schools in the city.

172
00:15:30,015 --> 00:15:31,616
So that's where my level of disagreement is.

173
00:15:31,676 --> 00:15:32,937
I'm not going to vote against

174
00:15:33,424 --> 00:15:37,827
free cash, but just the way this resolution is written, I don't agree with the second part.

175
00:15:37,987 --> 00:15:39,128
So I just want to clarify that.

176
00:15:39,348 --> 00:15:39,848
So thank you.

177
00:15:40,429 --> 00:15:41,309
Thank you, Councilor Merrill.

178
00:15:41,329 --> 00:15:41,990
Councilor Marks.

179
00:15:43,010 --> 00:15:59,141
Mr. President, also to clarify, the 6 point whatever it was, 2 or 3 million that the mayor did say she was going to take out of free cash does not change any of the circumstances which are currently taking place right now, which are the cuts within the city.

180
00:16:00,101 --> 00:16:00,921
and the school side.

181
00:16:01,481 --> 00:16:04,262
So anything else that happens would be in addition to that.

182
00:16:05,342 --> 00:16:09,403
So I think we've got to be mindful that six million brings us to where we are right now.

183
00:16:10,504 --> 00:16:12,544
And many of us want to go further than that.

184
00:16:13,064 --> 00:16:16,425
But, you know, we're going to have to wait and see.

185
00:16:16,485 --> 00:16:18,166
I think it is a wait and see game right now.

186
00:16:18,506 --> 00:16:27,848
And I've been saying that for the last month and a half regarding local receipts and regarding, you know, hopefully some type of bailout and so forth.

187
00:16:28,608 --> 00:16:30,108
So that's my hope, Mr. President.

188
00:16:30,469 --> 00:16:30,829
Thank you.

189
00:16:31,549 --> 00:16:32,569
Thank you, Councilor Marks.

190
00:16:34,189 --> 00:16:35,490
Anybody else like to speak on this issue?

191
00:16:35,510 --> 00:16:40,851
Okay, Clerk Cernovich, have you received any emails on this?

192
00:16:44,692 --> 00:16:45,852
I have not, Mr. President.

