1103
01:14:37,582 --> 01:14:47,347
So I'd like to take a second to talk to everyone about the need for police reform in the context of what we're seeing nationwide and locally here in the greater Boston area with protests.

1104
01:14:49,047 --> 01:14:51,969
I think everyone would agree that police are very important.

1105
01:14:52,329 --> 01:14:58,632
They have a dangerous job, and they have to go out and deal with many of kind of the worst

1106
01:14:59,624 --> 01:15:00,345
of our community.

1107
01:15:00,385 --> 01:15:03,367
When there's a problem, when there's a crime, they're the ones that get sent in.

1108
01:15:03,407 --> 01:15:05,349
They're the ones that have to go and deal with that.

1109
01:15:05,889 --> 01:15:12,855
And as a result, we give them a lot of leeway, and we cut them a lot of slack when it comes to how they interact with people.

1110
01:15:13,115 --> 01:15:16,638
They get licensed to use force that other people wouldn't be able to use.

1111
01:15:17,538 --> 01:15:22,682
And we give them the benefit of the doubt, so when something goes wrong, we tend to believe them.

1112
01:15:23,323 --> 01:15:28,167
But then things sometimes do go wrong, and sometimes they go wrong horribly, as we've seen multiple times

1113
01:15:29,060 --> 01:15:30,661
the nation with people getting killed.

1114
01:15:30,681 --> 01:15:38,167
We've seen George Floyd, Breonna Taylor, more recently, um, um, Brooks, I'm going to get his last, his first name wrong.

1115
01:15:38,588 --> 01:15:44,092
They were, they were killed at the hands of police and they, you know, these deaths didn't need to happen.

1116
01:15:44,973 --> 01:15:55,621
Um, and so there are protests that are happening nationwide that are protesting, not just these deaths, but kind of this system of violence and racism that seems to be targeting minorities in our community.

1117
01:15:56,404 --> 01:16:04,649
And so when we see these things, it's really easy to kind of look at that and think, well, those are other police forces.

1118
01:16:04,689 --> 01:16:05,990
Those are other parts of America.

1119
01:16:06,010 --> 01:16:08,731
It's not here in our community that we face these problems.

1120
01:16:09,312 --> 01:16:12,814
And I believe that these problems do exist in our community as well.

1121
01:16:13,314 --> 01:16:20,538
And the easiest evidence of this that we can see is the overtime scandal that happened recently that I'm sure everyone here is familiar with.

1122
01:16:20,989 --> 01:16:27,054
where multiple police officers were going and they were effectively stealing taxpayer money.

1123
01:16:27,735 --> 01:16:33,079
And the resolution of that was that none of these police officers were held accountable.

1124
01:16:33,119 --> 01:16:34,040
None of them were fired.

1125
01:16:34,100 --> 01:16:35,481
So they're all still on the force.

1126
01:16:35,521 --> 01:16:40,185
And in fact, I believe roughly a quarter of the police force now is on the Brady list.

1127
01:16:40,722 --> 01:16:51,509
which is a list of untrustworthy police officers that are not allowed to testify in a court of law because they're seen as untrustworthy actors.

1128
01:16:51,889 --> 01:16:53,911
And so their testimony isn't useful.

1129
01:16:53,991 --> 01:16:59,694
So a quarter of the police department can't even go to court to testify in the cases that they might be involved in.

1130
01:17:00,955 --> 01:17:08,760
And so in that context, I think it's important to think about what we're doing to reform police and maybe move things within Medford and within our own community.

1131
01:17:09,994 --> 01:17:15,998
The mayor recently sent out an open letter with Chief Buckley about how they're going to be doing more police training.

1132
01:17:16,359 --> 01:17:17,379
And I welcome that.

1133
01:17:17,439 --> 01:17:18,140
It's a good start.

1134
01:17:18,220 --> 01:17:18,980
It's not sufficient.

1135
01:17:19,581 --> 01:17:23,604
I've actually communicated with the mayor a bit more, and I believe that there are more things happening.

1136
01:17:24,204 --> 01:17:32,350
Chief Buckley is going to be going and reviewing policies and posting them publicly on the police website so there's greater transparency, and I greatly applaud that.

1137
01:17:33,010 --> 01:17:39,395
And I believe that the mayor is also going to go and declare racism to be a public health emergency.

1138
01:17:39,889 --> 01:17:44,893
And I'm not totally sure what the fallout of that is, but it certainly sounds good.

1139
01:17:45,334 --> 01:17:46,755
I think we need to go further, though.

1140
01:17:47,223 --> 01:17:49,985
And in particular, there are two things that I'm advocating for.

1141
01:17:50,005 --> 01:17:54,047
One is kind of on the prevention side, and one is on the accountability side.

1142
01:17:54,508 --> 01:18:00,792
On the prevention side, we should implement the policies that you can see at the aidcantwait.org website.

1143
01:18:01,132 --> 01:18:04,254
I'm going to quickly run through those right now, just so people know what they are.

1144
01:18:04,534 --> 01:18:07,856
These were just implemented in Somerville, so they work locally.

1145
01:18:08,076 --> 01:18:09,998
And we should be implementing all of them here.

1146
01:18:10,018 --> 01:18:14,881
And those policies specifically are a ban on chokeholds and strangleholds.

1147
01:18:15,512 --> 01:18:19,176
A requirement that police must try to deescalate the situation.

1148
01:18:19,196 --> 01:18:23,021
A requirement that the police must warn before firing shots.

